CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "Mary Dee, founder of the D.I.'s, flew in from Philadelphia for the big fashion show-dance, Sunday night, Jan. 28. She took the mike for a quick 'hello' to her devoted admirers."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mary Dee holding microphone, standing in Holiday House for D. I. Club's "Melody in Fashion" benefit for MENDS
